SIMPLE: whistler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whistler
<hw>Whis"tler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hwistlere</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, whistles, or produces or a
whistling sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The ring
ousel.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The widgeon.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The golden-eye.</def> <sd>(d)</sd>
<def>The golden plover and the gray plover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The hoary, or northern, marmot
(<spn>Arctomys pruinosus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The whistlefish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whistlewing</ent>⟦br⟧
